name: Ella Schwarz
details: Hi everyone! I'm Ella, and I'm one of the EECS16A coordinators for this semester. I'm a CS and Math double major, with a research focus in digital design and computer architecture. Outside of CSM, I'm a TA for EECS 151 and I do undergraduate research with SLICE lab. When I'm not responding to the 10 billion slack messages I get per hour, I like to watch dead by daylight streams on twitch and build low-efficiency farms in minecraft.

name: Bryan Ngo

details: Hi!! I'm Jordan, and I'm a junior from the Bay Area. In addition to teaching, in my free time I like to crochet, cook and bake, play board games, and swing dance!! I'm super excited to be in CSM again this semester :))

In my free time, I like playing golf, flying drones/video editing, drawing, and hiking. Feel free to reach out with any questions and I’m excited to meet y’all!

name: Ryan Nuqui
details: Hi y’all! I hope you are doing well :) My name is Ryan and I am a Computer Science & Applied Math major. I’m super excited to be teaching 61B again (this will be my fifth time as a 61B(L) TA). CS 61B was the class that made me want to do Computer Science and I hope that I can help make your experience great too. In my free time, I like to try out different restaurants, play board games with friends, and watch movies. Please feel free to chat if you have questions about CS, places to eat in Berkeley, or if you want weird film recs :)
